{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Remove UK-F Registration Requirement for Dual Citizens with British Fathers",
        "additional_details": "With new restrictions on dual citizen travel, those who are unable to access either a British Passport or a Certificate of Entitlement are now unable to travel using their non-UK passports.\r\nWe believe that for those who have previously enjoyed a dual citizen life, those who have solely lived/worked/studied in the UK and are now forced to pay \u00a3130, provide biometrics and a attend a citizenship ceremony pledging allegiance to the state and king could be made to feel like foreigners in their own home, and this removes right to travel.",
        "background": "Remove the requirement of UK-F Registration for children of unmarried British Fathers, who may have lived their entire lives in the UK, and who may have little to no ties to their other nationality.",
